1.Map function

Syntax:map(function,iterable..)

Parameters of map function:
	• function: The function or lambda expression you want to execute for each element in the iterable.
	• iterable: One or more iterables (lists, tuples, sets, etc.) whose elements will be passed to the function.
	💡 Note: map() returns a map object (which is an iterator). To see the actual results as a list, you need to pass it into the list() function.

